726501f-c.title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Caldwell Avenue
726501f-c.text:
Dry Parbor Road, east side, opposite Caldwell Avenue, showing
in three views the H. Hawkhurst house of 1860, also known as the
Brand house. See other viewa for more data. View No. 1 shows
Caldwell Avenue in the foreground with Dry Harbor Road, cutting
across house and barn.
April 1923

726499f-a.title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Caldwell Avenue
726499f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, (left of house, not shown) east side, Opposite
Caldwell Avenue (formerly Johnson Avenue) showing in three views the
H. Hawkhurst house of 1860. F. Brand was the owner from 1891-1896.
Views two and three show the outbuildings and near of the house. A
series of two story brick structures occupied this property in 1929.
April 1923
Views 1 and 2
View 3: May 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

726498f-a.title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Caldwell Avenue
726498f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, north side, east of Caldwell Avenue
and viewing fn that direction. The land and farm buildings
were owned by Kogelsberger (Kochesberger) in 1891 and 1909.
When 84th Street will be cut through the farmhouse will then
be at the N.E. corner of that street and the barns will be in
its path.
P. L. Sperr  July 2, 1935
